# 5. このままでいいのかな

An: I'm glad Soma let us know what's going on...
Toya: Me too...
Toya: Still...
Toya: To think that Tono may never return to this city...
Akito: ...
Kohane: Isn't there any other way...?
Kohane: All we can do is try to get better... But we don't have any good ideas for how to do that...
Akito: I know... I feel like we're at a dead end.
Akito: But all we can do now is try even harder...
Akito: Just try and try... And believe that our hard work will eventually be rewarded...
Kohane: Right...
An: We're definitely in a tough pickle... Even just today, we've been through a lot.
An: Hey, what if we stopped somewhere to take a break? Something sweet might help take our mind off things.
Akito: Yeah... I agree.
MEIKO: Oh! Welcome, everyone.
Kohane: Good evening, MEIKO...
Miku: None of you look very happy...
Miku: You just went to visit Soma at the hospital, right? What did you all talk about?
An: Oh, um... We talked about Arata.
An: According to Soma...
MEIKO: I see... It's unfortunate to hear that he's left the city.
KAITO: Yes, it's sad since we all thought your greater group was doing so well...
Kohane: Our group...
Kohane: ...
Kohane: This is so frustrating...
Len: What...?
Kohane: Oh, umm...
Kohane: What I mean is...
Kohane: I agree with KAITO... I thought we had a good thing going with Tono and the others...
Kohane: We all worked so hard... And our third event ended up becoming a big success.
Kohane: I really thought we could surpass RAD WEEKEND with them by our side.
Kohane: And yet, I...
Kohane: I couldn't do anything that time...
Kohane: My legs collapsed under me. I felt so powerless...
Kohane: But...
Kohane: That time... If only I hadn't given up... If only I sang with everything I had...
Kohane: Things might've turned out differently...
Kohane: We might've been able to get the others to stay. Even just one of them...
An: Kohane...
Kohane: Taiga's someone who performs all around the world... It only makes sense that he was able to defeat us so easily...
Kohane: But I can't help but feel...
Kohane: Really frustrated. If only I did something different that time...
Kohane: At the same time, I know there's no use crying over spilled milk...
Miku: (I see. Kohane's...)
Miku: You've changed so much, Kohane.
Kohane: What...?
